Author: Robert Wirth [aut], Moritz Schaaf [aut, cre], Solveig Tonn [aut],
    Roland Pfister [aut]
Maintainer: Moritz Schaaf <moritz.schaaf@uni-wuerzburg.de>
Description: Tool helping psychologists and other behavioural scientists
    analyze mouse movement (and other 2-D trajectory) data. Bundles together 
    several functions that compute spatial measures (MAD, AUC) or provide 
    a shorthand for often-used procedures. 'wuelib' is maintained by the 
    Cognition & Behaviour team of the University of Wuerzburg.
License: GPL (>= 3)
URL: https://github.com/mc-schaaf/wuelib,
